<subSubSection box="[151,504,295,322]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,504,295,322]" box="[151,504,295,322]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,504,295,322]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="2" pageNumber="471" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,504,295,322]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Leach, 1818" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1818" box="[238,504,295,322]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cirolanidae" genus="Cirolana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="471" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,346,295,322]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">Cirolana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Leach, W. E." box="[353,504,295,321]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471" pagination="338 - 354" refId="ref7976" refString="Leach, W. E. (1818) Cymothoades. In: Cuvier, F. (Ed.), Dictionnaire des sciences naturelles. Paris and Strasbourg, 12, pp. 338 - 354." type="journal article" year="1818">Leach, 1818</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="471" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,367,1150]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,367,393]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1818" box="[274,374,367,393]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cirolanidae" genus="Cirolana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="471" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[274,374,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">Cirolana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be identified by having the following combination of relatively easy to observe characters: frontal lamina with a relatively wide and ventral flat surface, clypeus always flat (i.e., without ventral or anterior projecting blade), pleonite 5 always laterally entirely overlapped by pleonite 4; mandible incisor visibly broad, more than 0.5 mandible width (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Bruce, N. L. &amp; Hughes, L. E." box="[494,755,475,502]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471" pagination="1395 - 1407" refId="ref7512" refString="Bruce, N. L. &amp; Hughes, L. E. (2020) A new species of Neocirolana Hale, 1925 (Crustacea: Isopoda: Cirolanidae) collected during the Royal Society Expedition to Aldabra 1967 - 69, western Indian Ocean. Journal of Natural History, 54 (21 - 22), 1395 - 1407. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222933.2020.1797202" type="journal article" year="2020">Bruce &amp; Hughes 2020</bibRefCitation>
), pereopods all ambulatory (i.e., without marked flatting of articles or presence of long natatory setae), pereopods 1–3 without anterolateral margins of ischium and or merus strongly produced and pleopod 2 appendix masculina attached basally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,367,1150]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">
The concept of what constituted 
<taxonomicName authority="Leach, 1818" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1818" box="[575,828,583,609]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cirolanidae" genus="Cirolana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="471" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[575,675,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">Cirolana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Leach, W. E." box="[684,828,583,609]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471" pagination="338 - 354" refId="ref7976" refString="Leach, W. E. (1818) Cymothoades. In: Cuvier, F. (Ed.), Dictionnaire des sciences naturelles. Paris and Strasbourg, 12, pp. 338 - 354." type="journal article" year="1818">Leach, 1818</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, then with 114 species, was wholly revised by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bruce, N. L." pageId="2" pageNumber="471" pagination="945 - 966" refId="ref7300" refString="Bruce, N. L. (1981) Cirolanidae (Crustacea: Isopoda) of Australia: Diagnoses of Cirolana Leach, Metacirolana Nierstrasz, Neocirolana Hale, Anopsilana Paulian &amp; Debouteville, and three new genera - Natatolana, Politolana and Cartetolana. Australian Journal of Marine and Freshwater Research, 32, 945 - 966. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / MF 9810945" type="journal article" year="1981">Bruce (1981)</bibRefCitation>
, resulting in the genus including just 44 species. Since that time the genus has again grown, now the largest in the family with 144 species (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Sidabalok, C. &amp; Bruce, N. L." box="[540,831,655,682]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471" pagination="177 - 207" refId="ref8553" refString="Sidabalok, C. M &amp; Bruce, N. L. (2018 a) Review of the Cirolana ' pleonastica - group' (Crustacea: Isopoda: Cirolanidae) with description of four new species from the Indo-Malaysian region. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 66, 177 - 207." type="journal article" year="2018">Sidabalok &amp; Bruce 2018a</bibRefCitation>
), and in the course of that time it has been increasingly recognized that there are distinct groups within the genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Bruce, N. L." box="[827,964,691,717]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471" pagination="1 - 239" refId="ref7370" refString="Bruce, N. L. (1986) Cirolanidae (Crustacea: Isopoda) of Australia. Records of the Australian Museum, Supplement, 6, 1 - 239. https: // doi. org / 10.3853 / j. 0812 - 7387.6.1986.98." type="journal article" year="1986">Bruce 1986</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bruce, N. L." box="[977,1037,691,717]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471" pagination="47 - 66" refId="ref7459" refString="Bruce, N. L. (2004) New species of the Cirolana ' parva - group' (Crustacea: Isopoda: Cirolanidae) from coastal habitats around Nw Zealand. Species Diversity, 9, 47 - 66. https: // doi. org / 10.12782 / specdiv. 9.47" type="journal article" year="2004">2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sidabalok, C. &amp; Bruce, N. L." box="[1051,1338,691,718]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471" pagination="401 - 435" refId="ref8492" refString="Sidabalok, C. &amp; Bruce, N. L. (2017) Review of the species of the Cirolana ' parva - group' (Cirolanidae: Isopoda: Crustacea) in Indonesian and Singaporean waters. Zootaxa, 4317 (3), 401 - 435. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4317.3.1" type="journal article" year="2017">Sidabalok &amp; Bruce 2017</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sidabalok, C. &amp; Bruce, N. L." box="[1351,1425,691,717]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471" pagination="177 - 207" refId="ref8553" refString="Sidabalok, C. M &amp; Bruce, N. L. (2018 a) Review of the Cirolana ' pleonastica - group' (Crustacea: Isopoda: Cirolanidae) with description of four new species from the Indo-Malaysian region. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 66, 177 - 207." type="journal article" year="2018">2018a</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Sidabalok, C. M." box="[151,346,727,753]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471" refId="ref8329" refString="Sidabalok, C. M. (2019) Systematics, phylogeny and distribution of Cirolanidae (Crustacea: Isopoda) of Indonesia and adjacent waters. Vol. PhD. Centre for Sustainable Tropical Fisheries &amp; Aquaculture. James Cook University, Townsville, xxii + 295 pp." type="book" year="2019">Sidabalok (2019)</bibRefCitation>
demonstrated that there are five definable monophyletic clades within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1818" box="[1148,1248,727,753]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cirolanidae" genus="Cirolana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="471" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1148,1248,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">Cirolana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, each clade supported by definable synapomorphies.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,367,1150]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">
One such clade was termed the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1818" box="[553,653,799,825]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cirolanidae" genus="Cirolana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="471" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[553,653,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">Cirolana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
‘ 
<emphasis box="[669,798,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">pleonastica</emphasis>
-group’ by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sidabalok, C. &amp; Bruce, N. L." box="[922,1234,799,826]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471" pagination="177 - 207" refId="ref8553" refString="Sidabalok, C. M &amp; Bruce, N. L. (2018 a) Review of the Cirolana ' pleonastica - group' (Crustacea: Isopoda: Cirolanidae) with description of four new species from the Indo-Malaysian region. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 66, 177 - 207." type="journal article" year="2018">Sidabalok &amp; Bruce (2018a)</bibRefCitation>
; both new species described here belong to that group. The critical apomorphic characters that define the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1818" box="[1110,1210,835,861]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cirolanidae" genus="Cirolana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="471" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1110,1210,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">Cirolana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
‘ 
<emphasis box="[1225,1354,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">pleonastica</emphasis>
-group’ include: rostral point absent, transverse sutures present on all or most pereonites, pleonites 3 and 4 with small nodules, uropod endopod with setae on distal third, and uropodal exopod lateral margin with three widely spaced relatively slender robust setae. There are several other characters consistently shown by species of this group, including all species in the group with the lateral margins of pleonite 3 not posteriorly produced, not overlapping pleonites 4 and 5 and the posterolateral margins (epimera) of pleonite 4 are posteriorly rounded. At present the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1818" box="[1336,1436,1015,1041]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cirolanidae" genus="Cirolana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="471" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1336,1436,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">Cirolana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
‘ 
<emphasis box="[161,290,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">pleonastica</emphasis>
-group’ has been recorded primarily from the tropical Indo-Pacific Ocean with one species from the Antarctic.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,367,1150]" box="[199,1062,1123,1150]" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">
Both new species described here belong to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1818" box="[725,825,1123,1149]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cirolanidae" genus="Cirolana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="471" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[725,825,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">Cirolana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
‘ 
<emphasis box="[841,970,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="471">pleonastica</emphasis>
-group’.
</paragraph>
